Create a .env file with these values 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server Configuration
PORT=5000

DB_USER=dbusername
DB_PASSWORD=your_passowrd
DB_NAME=task_manager
DB_NAME_TEST=task_manager_test
DB_NAME_PROD=task_manager_production
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_DIALECT=postgres
DB_PORT=5432

# JWT Secret Key
JWT_SECRET="YourJWTSecretcanbeanything"


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


To run the backend just use : 
npm start

This is will start the backend on PORT 5000 (by default i hardcoded the value as an option if you dont specify it in the env file just for development prurposes)

  
